{"cursor":"7517","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"The 'Thayer Learning Center' or 'TLC' was a military based, Christian boarding\nschool boot camp for troubled teens in Kidder, Missouri from 2002 to 2009. The\nprogram enrolled over 100 students and costs run up to $4,000 a month. The\nprogram stated that it \"...changes, reunites, and restores hope to families\nacross the nation.\" There has been some controversy in past\nyears.[http://www.isaccorp.org/thayerlearningcenter.asp] The center is one of\nmany facilities for troubled teens listed on the watch list on the International\nSurvivors Action Committee (ISAC).[http://www.isaccorp.org/ website]. For more\ninformation on the ISAC allegations, see the ISAC website\nhere.[http://www.isaccorp.org/thayerlearningcenter.asp].\n\nThe facility closed in September 2009. [http://www.citizen-\nobserver.com/articles/2009/09/03/news/doc4a9ffd9e583f7385995328.txt Former\nThayer Learning Center closes doors], By Andrew Bottrell, MyCameronnews.com,\nSeptember 3, 2009 In October 2009, it was announced that John and Willa\nBundy, of St. George, Utah had sold the grounds to Lakota John (also of St.\nGeorge) for the White Buffalo Academy, which is to focus on Native American\neducation. [http://www.kansascity.com/news/local/story/1515531.html\n] http://www.whitebuffaloacademy.com/\n\nThe campus was formerly Thayer College and a public school. Thayer College was\nfounded in 1871 and closed in 1876. It reopened in 1877 as the Kidder Institute\nand operated under the auspices of the Congregational Church of Missouri. The\nbuilding was used as a public school from 1934 to 1981.\n","linknr":145,"url":"Thayer_Learning_Center","recorded":1364155139,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Thayer_Learning_Center&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Thayer_Learning_Center&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//c